TOON_VERSION: 1.0
DOC_TYPE: UI_UX_SYSTEM
DOC_ID: printforge.uiux
TITLE: UI, UX, Visual Language, and Interaction Design

DESIGN_DIRECTION:
  Clean enterprise manufacturing software with strong visual hierarchy, quick situational awareness, and modern micro-interactions.
  It should feel more like a premium operations command center than a boring spreadsheet wrapper.

VISUAL_PRIORITIES:
  - readability first
  - real-time confidence
  - fast scanning
  - low cognitive overhead
  - premium but restrained
  - dark-mode excellence

AESTHETIC:
  - modern engineering dashboard
  - subtle glass, depth, and shadow layers
  - crisp cards and dense professional tables
  - animated status changes without gimmick overload
  - polished transitions similar to advanced design-system-grade SaaS products

COLOR_SYSTEM:
  semantic:
    - success = green family
    - warning = amber family
    - error = red family
    - info = blue family
    - neutral = zinc/slate family
  material_class:
    - filament = cool blue accent
    - resin = purple accent
    - high-risk material = orange or red accent border
  printer_status:
    - available = green
    - busy = blue
    - paused = amber
    - maintenance = purple
    - offline = slate
    - error = red

LAYOUTS:
  overview_dashboard:
    - top KPI strip
    - active project board
    - printer fleet grid
    - build queue panel
    - recent activity feed
  projects_page:
    - filter bar
    - kanban/list toggle
    - saved views
    - dense sortable table
  project_detail:
    - hero header
    - left summary rail
    - main tabbed workspace
    - right-side activity or blocker drawer optional
  printer_page:
    - card grid or table
    - occupancy overlays
    - maintenance badges
    - active job summary
  materials_page:
    - catalog table
    - faceted filters
    - comparison drawer
    - create/import actions

MOTION_RULES:
  - 150ms to 250ms for standard micro-interactions
  - 250ms to 400ms for panel transitions
  - use motion to reinforce state change, not decorate emptiness
  - animate status pills, drawer reveals, queue reorders, upload progress, and KPI count updates

COMPONENTS_REQUIRED:
  - app shell
  - responsive sidebar
  - sticky filter toolbar
  - KPI stat cards
  - kanban board
  - dense data table
  - file upload dropzone
  - preview cards
  - printer cards
  - material chips
  - timeline / activity feed
  - audit diff modal
  - multi-step create project wizard
  - modal to create build job
  - empty states
  - skeleton loaders
  - toast system
  - confirmation dialogs
  - search command palette

PRINTER_ICON_STRATEGY:
  - use local icon registry
  - each printer model gets a silhouette card image or SVG badge
  - support manufacturer pill next to model
  - expose iconKey so design system can map to custom assets later

PROJECT_CARD_FIELDS:
  - title
  - code
  - owner avatar/name
  - status
  - blocked badge
  - due date
  - current revision
  - printer target
  - material target
  - progress bar
  - quick action menu

UPLOAD_EXPERIENCE:
  - drag and drop
  - progress bar
  - checksum / duplicate hint
  - parsing state badge
  - preview thumbnail
  - mark as current revision action
  - revision compare entry

SEARCH_EXPERIENCE:
  global command palette should search:
    - projects
    - printers
    - materials
    - build jobs
    - users
    - file revisions

MOBILE_BEHAVIOR:
  - read-only dashboards and light edits should still work
  - primary optimization target remains desktop and tablet
  - printer assignment drawer and queue operations must remain usable on tablet in a print room

ACCESSIBILITY:
  - high contrast status badges
  - keyboard navigation for tables and dialogs
  - visible focus states
  - clear button labeling
  - non-color-only status indicators

COPY_TONE:
  - direct
  - operational
  - zero fluff
  - friendly but technical
  - use manufacturing wording that operators understand instantly

END_TOON